<div id="review_44376407" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/44376407" />
    <a title="Julie Suzanne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1505281-julie-suzanne"><img alt="Julie Suzanne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491956923p2/1505281.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/44376407?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julie Suzanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julie Suzanne" href="/user/show/1505281-julie-suzanne">Julie Suzanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1505281-julie-suzanne?shelf=abuse">abuse</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1505281-julie-suzanne?shelf=sports">sports</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1505281-julie-suzanne?shelf=suicide">suicide</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1505281-julie-suzanne?shelf=hs-library">hs-library</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer44376407" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1437932523678399603">Wow. <br/>I read this because another ELA teacher, grade 10 at another school, requires that her students read this. It was highly recommended by her years ago, and I found a copy and remembered. I wasn&apos;t hooked right away, and there was almost enough swimming/sport focus to ruin it, but there was enough drama to keep me interested. Eventually, there was no putting this down. We have intelligent male characters with great adult role models, much like John Green usually provides. Intelligent banter, i</span>
  <span id="freeText1437932523678399603" style="display:none">Wow. <br />I read this because another ELA teacher, grade 10 at another school, requires that her students read this. It was highly recommended by her years ago, and I found a copy and remembered. I wasn't hooked right away, and there was almost enough swimming/sport focus to ruin it, but there was enough drama to keep me interested. Eventually, there was no putting this down. We have intelligent male characters with great adult role models, much like John Green usually provides. Intelligent banter, intellectual discussions with inspiring teachers....this book was just right for this liberal who wants to live in a bubble. Serious issues were handled well, and it was genuinely exciting and thought-provoking. I highly recommend to "teens who care." Extremely satisfying. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1437932523678399603" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review44376407">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
