<div id="review_651419314" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/651419314" />
    <a title="Say" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7613621-say"><img alt="Say" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627157957p2/7613621.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/651419314?book_show_action=true">Jun 26, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Say" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Say" href="/user/show/7613621-say">Say</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer651419314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6200870154102553949">2.5 stars.<br/>Although this book gives off a John Green Vibe, the author cramps around five social issues into one book which makes the story a bit too far-fetched.<br/>I really only started enjoying it after I reached the mid-point. And then the author took the liberty to give it a completely abrupt ending.<br/><br/>Sarah Byrnes&apos; character will have you shedding tears for her and Moby is kind of like the friend you always wished you had in school.<br/><br/>The characters are closer to home and easy to relate to.<br/>Worth readi</span>
  <span id="freeText6200870154102553949" style="display:none">2.5 stars.<br />Although this book gives off a John Green Vibe, the author cramps around five social issues into one book which makes the story a bit too far-fetched.<br />I really only started enjoying it after I reached the mid-point. And then the author took the liberty to give it a completely abrupt ending.<br /><br />Sarah Byrnes' character will have you shedding tears for her and Moby is kind of like the friend you always wished you had in school.<br /><br />The characters are closer to home and easy to relate to.<br />Worth reading if you're a misfit (I know I am) or have ever accused anyone else of being one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6200870154102553949" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
